<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>Refugees in Croatia are being <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PROGRESSIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">refused</EVENT> burial rights  in Zagreb cemeteries and may only be <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="may">cremated</EVENT>, the Helsinki-based Human Rights  Committee <EVENT eid="e3" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE">Saturday</TIMEX3>.&#13;
The committee <EVENT eid="e4" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> the <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">ruling</EVENT>, which it <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">condemned</EVENT> as a "gross violation of  human and religious rights," had been <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">made</EVENT> by municipal authorities in Zagreb  <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE">last autumn</TIMEX3>.&#13;
The organisation <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">deplored</EVENT> that "those who have <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">lost</EVENT> everything <EVENT eid="e10" class="PERCEPTION" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">see</EVENT>  themselves <EVENT eid="e11" class="I_STATE" tense="PASTPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">deprived</EVENT> of two square metres of Croat land for their last resting  place."&#13;
Cemetery authorities <EVENT eid="e12" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">confirmed</EVENT> the policy, which they <EVENT eid="e13" class="I_ACTION" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">attributed</EVENT> to a  shortage of funeral grants, and <EVENT eid="e14" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> in a statement people that refugees and  displaced persons could be <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="could">buried</EVENT> at Velika Gorica cemetery in a Zagreb suburb  for a fee of 670 German marks (some 400 dollars).&#13;
More than 500,000 refugees have <EVENT eid="e16" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">fled</EVENT> to Croatia, most of them from  Bosnia-Herzegovina.&#13;
